            <p>This, while the opposing team does everything in their power to stop the other side getting into their end zone and trying to get their own touchdown in the other's end zone.<br><br>
                To be able to "sack" an opposing quarterback is getting into their defensive pocket (their stronghold during a forward drive) and bringing the quarterback to the floor. Pressurizing the quarterback means the quarterback cannot make successful plays and is obstructed from driving to the end zone of the opposing side.</p>

